## The Fake Database

`src/lib/mock/projects.ts` is your entire database right now. It's just two JS arrays:

- `STATIC_PROJECTS` — the two hand-written projects (Internship Search, Japan Trip) that always exist
- `dynamicProjects` — an empty array that gets projects pushed into it during the app session

It exports three functions: `getProjectById`, `getAllProjects`, `addProject`. Those are the only three things the API routes ever call. When Supabase comes, you delete this file and swap those three functions for DB queries. Nothing else changes.

**Critical thing to know:** `dynamicProjects` is just a variable in memory. Every time the server restarts it goes back to `[]`. New projects you create only survive until you refresh.

