## The API Routes

`src/app/api/` — these run **on the server only**, never in the browser. They're the wall between the browser and the mock store.

**`POST /api/projects`** — called when the modal finishes. Receives the draft, generates a `mock-<timestamp>` ID, returns `{ id }`. It does NOT save the draft content anywhere. Just hands back an ID.

**`GET /api/projects/[id]`** — called when any project page loads. Calls `getProjectById(id)`. Returns the project or 404. Right now this 404s for newly created projects because of the navigation bug — the page hits this endpoint before the project has been saved.

**`PUT /api/projects/[id]`** — called after generation is complete. Receives the full generated `Project` object, stamps the URL's ID onto it, calls `addProject()`. This is the moment a new project actually becomes findable.

**`GET /api/projects`** — returns all projects, used by the sidebar.

