## The Client API Layer

`src/lib/api/projects.ts` — these run **in the browser**. They're just `fetch()` wrappers with proper TypeScript types. There's no logic here, just HTTP calls to the routes above.

The one exception is `generateProjectPlan()` — it doesn't call an API route yet. It waits 3 seconds (so the animation plays) then returns hardcoded `MOCK_PHASES`. The TODO comment says swap this for a real call to `/api/ai` which would hit Anthropic. That's where the actual AI integration goes.

