## The Tasks System (separate thing)

`src/context/TaskContext.tsx` — React Context that holds all standalone tasks for the whole app. Fetches from `/api/tasks` once when the app loads, keeps a local copy. Today/Upcoming/Labels all read from this same context so they stay in sync. The optimistic update pattern means: flip the state immediately in the browser, then call the API. If the API fails, roll it back.

This has nothing to do with project phase tasks. Project tasks live inside `project.phases[n].tasks` and are fetched as part of the project. They're a separate thing.

